The paper deals with Structure from Motion (SfM) approaches, which are commonly used in computer vision and graphics. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.GR (Graphics) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses parallel computing and optimization methods, which are relevant to cs.RO (Robotics and Control) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Finally, the paper presents a novel approach for bundle adjustment, which involves statistical methods and optimization, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a possible sub-category as well.
